

	 
       Five minutes of Love  At One o'clock I sit in bed I think of all the things I should have said Conversations spinning in my head  At One O' one I grab my phone But all I hear is a dialtone  Now at One O'two I lay back down I lay in silence, but hear a sound  Someone wispers "I love you" in my ear I open my eyes and there forms a tear  You sit beside me on my bed You explain the things you wish you'd said  At One O' five I stare at you I look deep into your eyes and say "I love you too".
     
    
